        <div class="history-left scroll-fade-left">
            <img src="img/history1.png">
            <h2>🕰 Our Story Since 1902</h2>
            <p>The story of Hotel Seetha began in 1902, when a humble family guest house opened its doors to travelers passing through the region. At that time, the area was a quiet resting place for merchants, pilgrims, and visitors seeking warmth and rest during their journeys. The founders a kind-hearted local family believed that hospitality was more than service; it was about caring for people like family.</p>
        <br>
         <p>Over the years, the small rest house grew in reputation, known for its genuine kindness, delicious home-cooked meals, and a peaceful environment that made guests return again and again. As decades passed, Hotel Seetha evolved to meet the changing needs of travelers while preserving the same heartwarming traditions that began over a century ago.</p>
       <br>
       <p>Through wars, modernization, and the passing of generations, Hotel Seetha has stood proudly as a symbol of enduring Sri Lankan hospitality. The charm of our early beginnings still lives within our walls from the warm smiles that greet you at the door to the peaceful comfort found in every room.
Today, Hotel Seetha combines the elegance of its historical roots with the conveniences of modern living. Our beautifully furnished rooms are designed with your comfort in mind, offering air-conditioning, free Wi-Fi, cozy interiors, and everything you need for a relaxing stay. We take pride in providing not only a place to rest, but a place to feel at home.</p>
      <br>
      <p>Our mission has always been to make every guest feel valued, respected, and cared for. From our attentive staff to our high standards of cleanliness and service, we ensure that each moment you spend with us is pleasant and meaningful.
Whether you're here for a peaceful vacation, a business trip, or a family retreat, Hotel Seetha welcomes you with open arms just as we have done for travelers since 1902. With over a century of history and a heart full of hospitality, we continue to create beautiful memories for guests from around the world.</p>
   
